  "prompt": "How do you see the PM Modi\u2019s move of banning old 500 and 1000 rupee currency notes?",
  "response": "The demonetization move by PM Modi in November 2016 was a complex and controversial decision with mixed outcomes. Here are some perspectives:\n\nPositive Aspects:\n1. Aimed to curb black money and counterfeit currency\n2. Promoted digital transactions and financial transparency\n3. Potentially reduced corruption\n4. Increased tax compliance\n\nNegative Aspects:\n1. Significant economic disruption\n2. Short-term cash shortage and economic slowdown\n3. High implementation challenges\n4. Caused significant inconvenience to common people\n5. Informal and cash-dependent sectors were severely impacted\n\nEconomists and experts have diverse opinions about its overall effectiveness. While the intention was noble, the execution and immediate economic consequences were widely debated. The long-term impact remains a topic of discussion among economic analysts.\n\nUltimately, the move's success is viewed differently by various stakeholders, with valid arguments on both sides.",
